All dependencies required to run any explanation:
note: using NodeJS for example, these commands probably are not necessary 

yarn:

init (create package.json)
add @babel/cli (allow babel's commands)
add @babel/preset-env (install babel dependencies(need to put in .babelrc as preset))
add @babel/core
add @babel/plugin-proposal-object-rest-spread(need to put in .babelrc as plugin)
add webpack webpack-cli -D
add babel-loader@8.0.0-beta.0 -D (to run into webpack)
add webpack-dev-server -dependencies
add @babel/plugin-transform-async-to-generator -D
add @babel/polyfill -D

